A byte is composed out of two nibbles <0-F> 4F, 3C,...
one nibble is 4 bits (0 or 1) 

A nibble:
0001 -> 1 == 1
0010 -> 2 == 2
0100 -> 4 == 4
1000 -> 8 == 8

1111 - > 1 + 2 + 4 + 8 = 15 == F

A whole byte:

nibble 1 + nibble 2
0100 + 1111
4 + F

01001111 = 4F == O
